article.headline: Pennsylvania 19, Drexel 73
article.story: PHILADELPHIA (AP) -- Jeff Schiffner scored 20 points and Adam Chubb added a career-high 19 as Penn held off neighborhood rival Drexel 79-73 Monday night. Kenell Sanchez scored 17 points and Phil Goss 15 for Drexel, playing its first game of the season. Penn (1-1) never trailed, and led by as many as 19 points in the first half, before the Dragons closed to 54-48 on a 3-pointer by Goss with 10:28 to play. The Quakers then moved out to a 70-59 advantage on two free throws by Chubb at the 3:00 mark before Drexel rallied to 75-71 with 11 seconds to go. Two free throws by Schiffner one second later sealed the victory. Leading 16-15, Penn ran off 12 straight points to take a 28-15 lead midway through the first half, and built the margin to 35-19. Drexel scored eight unanswered points but Chubb hit four straight free throws, helping the Quakers to build a 42-31 halftime lead. Drexel upset the Quakers 71-62 last season, but Penn still holds a 12-4 advantage in the all-time series.
